<span id="freeTextContainer11569063233522659799">I don&apos;t usually read nonfiction, but this book grabbed me right from the start. I couldn&apos;t put it down. The author&apos;s account of the destruction of his country was stunning. I felt his pain as he compared the land where he grew up to the present day devastation. It made me want to read more on what was happening there right now.<br/></span>
