<div id="review_1009129028" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1009129028" />
    <a title="Judy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7074319-judy"><img alt="Judy" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1009129028?book_show_action=true">Jul 28, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Judy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Judy" href="/user/show/7074319-judy">Judy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780330507769" href="/book/show/9141015-the-fear">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1009129028" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16904078514359529421">I finished this book about a week ago and have delayed writing a review because I find it very difficult to put my response into words.<br/><br/>First, though, Peter Godwin, and the people who told their stories deserve huge credit for doing what it took to gather this information and write the book. <br/><br/>Because there is so much horror in many parts of the world, I know people become inured to it, and what Godwin writes of might not be regarded as exceptional... But Zimbabwe will always be my home country, ev</span>
  <span id="freeText16904078514359529421" style="display:none">I finished this book about a week ago and have delayed writing a review because I find it very difficult to put my response into words.<br /><br />First, though, Peter Godwin, and the people who told their stories deserve huge credit for doing what it took to gather this information and write the book. <br /><br />Because there is so much horror in many parts of the world, I know people become inured to it, and what Godwin writes of might not be regarded as exceptional... But Zimbabwe will always be my home country, even though I left it 14 years ago. So it matters a lot to me.<br /><br />The book raises observations and questions: many people who live in Zimbabwe don't talk of what goes on. Can it truly be that they don't know? Don't want to know? Perhaps feel too much shame to want to talk about it? (Not that the shame is theirs.) Some of the most evil aspects must be the deliberate sanctioning and the cowardice of the perpetrators of this horror.<br /><br />For now, I really don't feel I can do justice to a good enough review of this book, but I would urge people to read it because it is the truth and it should be known.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16904078514359529421" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


