<div id="review_546644651" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/546644651" />
    <a title="Patrick Carroll" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16771117-patrick-carroll"><img alt="Patrick Carroll" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1359064631p2/16771117.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/546644651?book_show_action=true">Feb 26, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patrick Carroll" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patrick Carroll" href="/user/show/16771117-patrick-carroll">Patrick Carroll</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780330507769" href="/book/show/9141015-the-fear">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer546644651" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3257638873645003138">This is not a pleasant or easy read, but it provides insight into what tyranny means within a country and the slow disintegration of a society. Peter Godwin clearly loves Zimbabwe and its people and like his readers is forced to sit impotently by and watch the steady erosion of its potential under the rule of someone totally corrupted by power. The big question is can Zimbabwe avoid the final collapse into a failed state? The Government of national Unity may be a transitionary step but equally i</span>
  <span id="freeText3257638873645003138" style="display:none">This is not a pleasant or easy read, but it provides insight into what tyranny means within a country and the slow disintegration of a society. Peter Godwin clearly loves Zimbabwe and its people and like his readers is forced to sit impotently by and watch the steady erosion of its potential under the rule of someone totally corrupted by power. The big question is can Zimbabwe avoid the final collapse into a failed state? The Government of national Unity may be a transitionary step but equally it may simply draw the nascent opposition into more exposure and vulnerability. Bearing in mind that 4 years have past since the "elections" there is perhaps hope that some form of transition might be effected after all Uncle Bob isn't immortal however will the power vacuum he leaves lead to an explosive collapse or not? The astounding thing in this book are the simple everyday tales of heroism from those who won't be cowed, contracted against so many who have decided that siding with the "bully" is the better survival mechanism. Immensely sad to read about so much evil.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3257638873645003138" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


