    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_160015819" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/160015819" />
    <a title="Melissa Acuna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3445700-melissa-acuna"><img alt="Melissa Acuna" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/160015819?book_show_action=true">Apr 10, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissa Acuna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissa Acuna" href="/user/show/3445700-melissa-acuna">Melissa Acuna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer160015819" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11587009313840753843">The Fear is horrific and necessary. Peter Godwin details the systematic, state sponsored torture and terrorism in his native country of Zimbabwe. He recounts the stories of survivors with little flourish, just the simple language and details that are provided to him, making the events even more difficult and unimaginable. He&apos;s well-connected and has access to many leaders within the opposition, providing excellent political analysis and background to the situation with Mugabe&apos;s dictatorship. <br/><br/>Des</span>
  <span id="freeText11587009313840753843" style="display:none">The Fear is horrific and necessary. Peter Godwin details the systematic, state sponsored torture and terrorism in his native country of Zimbabwe. He recounts the stories of survivors with little flourish, just the simple language and details that are provided to him, making the events even more difficult and unimaginable. He's well-connected and has access to many leaders within the opposition, providing excellent political analysis and background to the situation with Mugabe's dictatorship. <br /><br />Despite his beautiful writing, I had to read this in small doses or it was over-whelming. All that said, this should be on everyone's 2011 reading list. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11587009313840753843" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


